# `apps/web` — English and Spanish (next-intl)

You are editing the Next.js app under `apps/web/`.

- **Locales:** Route prefixes **`/en`** and **`/es`** (see existing next-intl setup).
- **User-facing copy:** Do **not** hardcode strings in components. Add or reuse keys in the project’s message catalogs and use next-intl APIs (`useTranslations`, etc.) per existing patterns in this app.
- **Scope:** Applies to any UI shown to end users (labels, buttons, errors, empty states, validation messages).
- **Consistency:** Match naming and file layout already used for translations in this package; do not introduce a second i18n system.

For product-wide context, see `CONTEXT.md` and the main `project.mdc` rule.
